  1)It is a Graphical user interface which is basically a display with things like frames and button and it allows users to do activities and interact on

  2) Event driven programming is when the flow of program execution is determined by events. Examples would be a user's actions like pressing keys or a message from the operating system.

  3)When you add components directly to a frame you actually add components to a panel by default. So in reality there is no difference for adding components to the frame 

  4) Jlabels are used to display text and cannot be changed by the user 

  5)Its mandatory because most swing objects are not thread safe. Pulling multiple threads risks memory consistency errors.
  

  6)A button is what the user interacts with to submit information and the label is what displays that answer or results 
  
